metadata.name: FAT Christmas #579
metadata.description:
“FAT Christmas” 由三位台灣創作者主導，並且與另外幾位創作者共創部件。包含發行過 Moonlight Impression 的 mido、影像創作者 Graphyni、熱衷 AI 生成的 Fagem。
你可以在這個生成器中獲取 Chang Ming Yao 的 Aka’s Ape 或由 Chi.L 繪製的 AKAZOO Cat，甚至是 roupin_art 的 Dino Ali。
並祝福所有 Tezos 的創作者與藏家，接下來一年能充滿希望。

我們竭盡所能的補充多樣性，確保每次鑄造都是明確且獨特的結果。
在30多種的背景中，包含由創作者提供的特殊款式，如果你足夠幸運，將有機會獲得美麗且獨特的角色 。

角色方面：
Aka’s Ape 包含 8 種 character、8 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、3 種 personality。
Aka Zoo Cat 包含 7 種 character、10 種 eyes、7 種 mouth、5 種  personality。
Dino Ali 包含 26 種 character、5 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、6 種 personality。
所有角色共享超過 20 款頭飾、9 款服裝、10 種服裝印花。
角色前方桌面的三個位置，亦各自包含 10 種以上的配件。

由衷的希望各位都能玩得開心。
祝大家聖誕快樂，新年快樂。

“FAT Christmas” is a collabration of three creators from Taiwan, with parts contributed by creators including mido's “Moonlight Impression”, video creator Graphyni and generative AI enthusiast Fagem.
You can get Aka’s Ape by Chang Ming Yao, AKAZOO  Cat by Chi.L and Dino Ali by roupin_art from the generator.
Blessing to all Tezos creators and collectors, filled with hope in the coming year.

Diversity is replenished in our best effort to ensure apparent and unique results in every mint.
Among over 30 different backgrounds, including special design provided by the creators, you will have a chance to get a gorgeous and unique character if you are lucky enough.

About the characters:
Aka’s Ape includes 8 types of character, 8 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 3 types of personality.
Aka Zoo Cat includes 7 types of character, 10 types of eyes, 7 types of mouth and 5 types of personality.
Dino Ali includes 26 types of character, 5 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 6 types of personality.
All characters share over 20 headwears, 9 clothes and 10 clothes patterns.
Over 10 decorations will be assigned to 3 positions on the table in front of the character.

Sincerely hope everyone can have fun.
And wishing you all a Merry Christmas and a happy new year.

metadata.name: RAUSCH #150
metadata.description:
RAUSCH is a series of generative artworks that explore imaginary digital architectures. 

This series challenges traditional notions of architectural representation and raises important questions about the role of resolution in design. Just as the pixel resolution of an image affects its perceived quality, the resolution of an architectural space can affect its qualities and livability. By embracing digital variation through codes, this series explores the interplay between abstract and concrete space through multiple resolutions. 

RAUSCH is inspired by the feeling of being overwhelmed by complex, chaotic and messy sensations, and aims to engage the viewer through a sense of wonder, disorientation, and awe.

Released on the occasion of Companions of Code, a group exhibition by VerticalCrypto Art at The NFT Gallery in London. 
Curated by Micol Ap. Exhibition 10-24 February 2023 

___________________________________________________

• 'MouseClick' pause/play animation

Save & Export Image:

metadata.name: Contraformas #53
metadata.description:
Shapes are drawn on a space-filling grid against other shapes, using a random walk algorithm. then they are separated with a random offset, hence the name counterforms (contraformas).

created by @mdollinger with p5js

metadata.name: Cosmic reaction #101
metadata.description:
As per my daily programming routine, this time I went to combine different circle algorithms, like my last work. This work, by using the optimized algorithm of packing and fields and combining them with a pattern for the inner connection of the circles, presents an artwork with high details that can be seen in large dimensions by plotting it. There are different variations, some of which are more detailed. The colors of some circles, at much higher resolutions, may look very slightly different.
_________________________

To see the artwork in high quality, open it in live view and add “&res=1 to 25” to the URL, This artwork can also be plotted in large dimensions.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Flume #139
metadata.description:
Flume are infinitely flowing digital bodies of water.
The flow of Flumes can range from slow and gentle, creating small ripples and eddies, to fast and turbulent, carving its way through the inner workings of your computer screen. 
The color, clarity, and viscosity of the water can also vary.

This is the culmination of my collection Flume, an exploration into On-Chain art on Ethereum, https://etherscan.io/address/0x1fa23513825f952afca07a603ac3f312ebee4ca9

These pieces were all created in p5js.

- Andrew

metadata.name: NYC-80 #41
metadata.description:
Even if this work was intended as an abstract study, the crowded, rhythmically repeating structures are reminiscent of the monumental, anonymous appearance of some large cities.
The appearance is determined by naive strong strokes and simple forms that give the picture a strong and self-confident expressiveness reminiscent of the art of the New York art scene of the 80s. The surfaces are deliberately not layered, in order to underline the impenetrability, but also to preserve the abstract painterly element.

metadata.name: Gribouillis #107
metadata.description:
"Gribouillis" tends to reproduce the result of what you could draw without too much thinking on your sketchbook; an automatic drawing while listening to a call or podcast... Or something you would draw on the napkin of a restaurant without a strong focus...
Those kind of drawing that don't have a lot of meaning, but that, sometimes, give you find some comfort.

---

This is a "screenshot" of the current researches and work I'm doing to emulate a sensation of sketching.

---

Open the link and add '#hd' in the URL to have a A3 size of the artwork.

---

Made to run in browser, especially Chrome.
Works on most recent iPhones.

---

Twitter: @florianzumbrunn
Instagram: @florianzumbrunn

metadata.name: When we were Kids #114
metadata.description:
When we were kids.

A work that goes back to our childhood.
When I was a kid I loved spending time with my grandmother and parents, we took a lot of walks with them, looked at different houses, spent time in nature, painted and in general were very much involved in the creative component, it was my parents and grandmother who instilled in me a love for creativity.

Probably one of the few things that have survived to these days is my childhood drawings, a little funny, sloppy, but so real and sincere.

In this work I wanted to take me back to those carefree times and remember with what eagerness and zeal I tried every day to learn something new or to go further than before.

None of this would have happened without my family, for which I am truly grateful.

10% of primary sales will be donated to Cure Parkinson's, I hope all children will have a childhood where they can spend time with their loved ones.

Be patient, some variations take a little longer to render.

Press S for Save Canvas as PNG.

By aleks.ustya, @ALEKUSTN. Made with p5js.
